[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged with murder Alison Jane Farr-Davies Swansea

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with the murder of a 42-year-old woman whose body was found at a house in Swansea.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Alison Jane Farr-Davies, 42, was found dead at a home in Neath Road, Hafod, Swansea, on Tuesday afternoon.
South Wales Police said Dean Marcus Jones, 37, has been charged with her murder. He appeared before Swansea magistrates on Saturday.
Ms Farr-Davies would have turned 43 on Friday, a birthday she shared with her mother.
